# 🔌 Interface — Manager ↔ {{DEPT_NAME}}

> Async channel (`CLAUDE.md §2.3`). Sessions don't talk in real time: the committente
> transports (launches sessions, pull/push), but the **content** flows **here**, in git.
> Goal: nobody has to *remember* to update anybody — the protocol does it.
>
> **Protocol:**
> - **{{DEPT_NAME}} at start:** read `## 📥 From Manager` → do open `[ ]` requests.
> - **{{DEPT_NAME}} at close:** update `## 📍 Digest`, write news/requests in `## 📤 From {{DEPT_NAME}}`, check `[x]` what's closed, **commit + push** (only `{{DEPT_FOLDER}}/`).
> - **Manager at start & before every gate:** read `## 📍 Digest` + `## 📤 From {{DEPT_NAME}}`, answer/order in `## 📥 From Manager`, check `[x]`.
> Full state: `{{DEPT_FOLDER}}/STATUS.md` (this file is the **channel**, not the register).
> IDs: `#M<n>` (manager), `#{{DEPT_LETTER}}<n>` (department).

## 📍 Digest — {{DEPT_NAME}} (kept by the department)
- {{DATE}} — <1–3 lines of current state>. Detail: `{{DEPT_FOLDER}}/STATUS.md`

## 📥 From Manager → {{DEPT_NAME}} (requests / decisions / answers)
- [ ] `{{DATE}}` **#M1** — <request>

## 📤 From {{DEPT_NAME}} → Manager (updates / requests / questions)
- [ ] `{{DATE}}` **#{{DEPT_LETTER}}1** — <update or question>
